  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Peace from the Bottom up: Reinforcing Local Actions for Peace in the Kivus</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local peacebuilding organisations, including women&#x2019;s groups, are at the centre of the action and once identified and brought into the project, they will work with Alert to plan and implement the activities, including establishment of the Kivu-wide peacebuilding network and carrying out peace dialogues and advocacy. Key international peacebuilding organisations working in DRC will also be invited to the meetings and exchanges of the Kivus-wide peacebuilding network, where this is feasible and pertinent. This will include feeding outcomes from the peace dialogues and debates of the Kivus peace network to the North Kivu advocacy working group of INGOs, which is a sub-group of the Heads of Mission, in which International Alert is a key participant. At least four joint meetings of the Kivu Peace Network and the North Kivu advocacy working group will be organized, to discuss joint advocacy initiatives, and establish stronger connections between international and local NGOs for advocacy purposes. Finally, government, private sector, community and civil society actors at provincial, national and regional (Great Lakes) levels will be the targets of peace dialogues and advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Specific Objectives are (1) To strengthen local peace actors and processes in the Kivus, (2) To generate peacebuilding feedback and input from local levels to national, regional, and international policy</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support local peacebuilding actors in Eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) to initiate and lead a bottom-up, effective peace process. The project is implemented in Walikale, Masisi and Rutshuru Territories in North Kivu Province, and Kalehe Territory in South Kivu Province.</narrative>
  </description>
